This paper presents a novel algorithm for optimization, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in machine learning (cs.LG), optimization (cs.NE), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm is based on natural gradients, which are commonly used in optimization and machine learning. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of importance mixing, which is a technique used in statistics and probability theory, and may be of interest to researchers in data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the algorithm in control systems, which may be of interest to researchers in systems and control (cs.SY).
